53:42.820 --> 53:44.140
tra la cristiana

53:44.140 --> 53:46.740
o le relazioni tra la cristiana

53:46.740 --> 53:49.500
e il mondo islamico.

53:49.980 --> 53:54.100
Non credo che ci sia un classo di civilizzazioni.

53:54.520 --> 53:56.720
Penso che ci sia un classo di civilizzazioni

53:56.720 --> 53:59.300
se non siamo abbastanza intelligenti

53:59.300 --> 54:02.280
per capire che possiamo evitare.

54:02.280 --> 54:06.380
Ma dovete capire che la metodologia europea

54:06.380 --> 54:09.420
di come stiamo lavorando

54:10.300 --> 54:14.400
è l'instrumento di cooperazione

54:14.400 --> 54:15.980
con le persone di fuori dell'Unione.

54:16.920 --> 54:18.600
E quando ho avuto i cittadini nord europei

54:19.600 --> 54:21.040
o dei nostri leader,

54:21.340 --> 54:23.200
con tutti i valori che ho avuto per questo,

54:23.240 --> 54:24.440
ma insisto,

54:26.060 --> 54:30.220
dico che dobbiamo cooperare con te

54:30.220 --> 54:32.620
perché solo con la vostra cooperazione

54:33.060 --> 54:34.760
possiamo cooperare bene.

54:34.760 --> 54:37.740
E abbiamo un sviluppo comune

54:37.740 --> 54:39.740
e possiamo scambiare

54:39.740 --> 54:42.760
ogni storia del colonialismo

54:43.400 --> 54:45.520
su ogni problema e così via.

54:45.780 --> 54:47.940
Solo se restiamo insieme.

54:48.580 --> 54:51.140
E dobbiamo costruire istituzioni

54:51.140 --> 54:52.620
per l'interazione di cooperazione.

54:53.220 --> 54:55.220
E lo otterremo, lo otterremo,

54:55.320 --> 54:59.040
in grado dei problemi e degli ostacoli.

54:59.040 --> 55:02.040
E quindi,

55:03.360 --> 55:05.420
questo è il modo in cui l'Europa

55:05.420 --> 55:08.380
deve essere pronta per la nuova mobilizzazione,

55:08.840 --> 55:12.800
in modo da non disaparire dalla mappa del mondo

55:12.800 --> 55:15.020
e di essere un protagonisto nel futuro.

55:16.720 --> 55:18.320
Vi ricordo che siamo 500 milioni di persone,

55:18.900 --> 55:21.100
dovremo essere 500 milioni di persone

55:21.840 --> 55:24.740
e una grande cultura, una grande tradizione.

55:26.880 --> 55:30.920
Dovremo anche fare un esercito culturale.

55:34.460 --> 55:36.500
Non ho nulla contro le università americane,

55:37.080 --> 55:39.480
ma una delle mie sorprese,

55:39.700 --> 55:43.120
quando ero prime ministero

55:43.120 --> 55:44.820
nei relativi campi americani,

55:45.080 --> 55:48.500
è che tutti i miei colleghi erano studiati

55:48.500 --> 55:49.700
nelle università americane.

55:51.200 --> 55:54.160
E erano in amore con l'Europa,

55:54.160 --> 55:55.260
con la nostalgia,

55:56.160 --> 55:57.300
ma quando erano studiati?

55:57.300 --> 55:58.140
In Cicago.

55:58.640 --> 56:01.680
Questo è un risultato strano.

56:02.380 --> 56:05.600
Perché non siamo in grado di attrezzare

56:05.600 --> 56:08.480
il vero, di competere con gli Stati Uniti

56:08.480 --> 56:10.060
per attrezzare il vero, il più talentoso,

56:10.160 --> 56:11.220
di giovane persone nel mondo?

56:12.600 --> 56:13.600
Non penso così.

56:13.640 --> 56:16.320
Sì, dobbiamo mettere il nostro effetto insieme

56:16.320 --> 56:18.440
e creare tre o quattro, cinque,

56:18.440 --> 56:21.300
post-graduate sector in Europa,

56:21.340 --> 56:23.220
in cui c'è questa fermentazione,

56:23.820 --> 56:26.080
in cui abbiamo il stesso sapore internazionale

56:26.080 --> 56:28.420
che avevamo nella Università Bologna

56:28.420 --> 56:29.340
pochi settimane fa,

56:29.600 --> 56:30.860
che era più di ora,

56:31.140 --> 56:35.380
se guardiamo il nome dei studenti

56:35.380 --> 56:36.860
e la città da dove vengono,

56:36.900 --> 56:39.280
vengono davvero dal mondo

56:39.280 --> 56:41.300
che era conosciuto nel tempo.

56:41.780 --> 56:44.540
Dobbiamo tornare ai nostri roti,

56:45.720 --> 56:47.200
dobbiamo imparare dalla storia

56:47.200 --> 56:54.420
e credo che questo sia un strumento

56:54.420 --> 56:55.960
per risolvere questo problema.

56:58.620 --> 56:59.240
E voglio finire,

56:59.700 --> 57:02.640
tornando a quello che ho detto prima,

57:03.780 --> 57:05.880
che questo obiettivo può essere ottenuto

57:05.880 --> 57:08.380
solo per una cooperazione più profonda

57:08.380 --> 57:10.620
tra i Stati Uniti e l'Europa.

57:10.880 --> 57:13.000
Se non c'è questa cooperazione,

57:13.980 --> 57:16.320
il mondo sarà in fase

57:16.320 --> 57:18.800
di instabilità.

57:20.300 --> 57:21.060
Questo è quello che significa.

57:21.260 --> 57:21.680
Cosa significa?

57:21.800 --> 57:22.760
Che l'Europa e l'U.S.

57:22.860 --> 57:23.760
devono risolvere,

57:24.260 --> 57:26.480
ma anche noi insolvendo.

57:26.700 --> 57:27.260
La città dell'Europa

57:27.260 --> 57:29.300
è iniziata da WTO

57:30.160 --> 57:33.020
e tra i problemi dell'economia.

57:33.060 --> 57:33.980
Prima di scegliere,

57:34.140 --> 57:34.700
voglio ricordarvi,

57:34.960 --> 57:36.660
quando ho incontrato il Presidente Clinton

57:36.660 --> 57:40.760
e abbiamo proposto la sconfitta

57:40.760 --> 57:46.420
di canzonare le nostre customi,

57:46.560 --> 57:47.460
le nostre bellezza

57:47.460 --> 57:49.120
di tutte le rocce

57:49.120 --> 57:51.940
che vengono dalle migliori città

57:51.940 --> 57:53.760
del 43-44,

57:54.280 --> 57:55.820
le migliori città del mondo.

57:57.540 --> 57:58.900
E lo abbiamo quasi fatto.

57:59.320 --> 58:00.420
Poi c'erano problemi

58:00.420 --> 58:02.700
dentro l'U.S. e così via.

58:03.480 --> 58:04.720
Ma se lo avessimo fatto,

58:05.160 --> 58:06.760
probabilmente avremmo evitato

58:08.100 --> 58:09.160
il problema di Seattle.

58:09.160 --> 58:12.080
Perché se dimostriamo

58:12.080 --> 58:13.080
che il nostro leader

58:14.440 --> 58:17.340
è consente di problemi di altri,

58:17.400 --> 58:19.540
penso che la reazione

58:19.540 --> 58:20.420
sarebbe molto migliore

58:20.420 --> 58:22.780
di quella che abbiamo avuto.

58:23.020 --> 58:24.340
Quindi questo è il problema

58:25.340 --> 58:27.440
di cosa significa

58:27.440 --> 58:29.660
l'u.s.-uropa cooperazione

58:29.660 --> 58:30.320
nel mondo,

58:31.280 --> 58:32.220
che è la nostra sfida,

58:32.500 --> 58:35.880
perché questo tipo di problemi,

58:35.880 --> 58:38.040
l'Unione nazionale e WTO,

58:38.040 --> 58:39.160
non possono essere risolviti

58:39.160 --> 58:40.900
se non c'è una forte cooperazione

58:40.900 --> 58:44.140
tra l'U.S. e l'uropa.

58:44.400 --> 58:48.640
Quindi penso che,

58:49.660 --> 58:52.040
perché condividiamo

58:52.640 --> 58:54.040
il tipo di democrazia,

58:55.500 --> 58:56.340
la tradizione,

58:56.700 --> 58:58.340
la storia, le speranze,

58:58.760 --> 58:59.960
credo che avremo

58:59.960 --> 59:01.360
anche la responsabilità

59:01.360 --> 59:04.420
di condividere la responsabilità

59:04.420 --> 59:06.480
di creare una nuova politica.

59:06.480 --> 59:08.920
E questo è il gioco

59:08.920 --> 59:10.580
del XXI secolo.

59:16.080 --> 59:17.080
Grazie.

59:30.940 --> 59:31.940
Ok.

59:33.400 --> 59:34.140
No question?

59:36.560 --> 59:37.040
Ok.

59:40.520 --> 59:41.320
Grazie.

59:41.700 --> 59:42.140
Grazie.

59:45.520 --> 59:47.560
My name is Isabella Nobili.

59:47.660 --> 59:49.020
I'm a graduate student

59:49.020 --> 59:50.500
at the University of Padua

59:50.500 --> 59:52.520
in Forestry and Environmental Sciences.

59:53.100 --> 59:54.620
I will have

59:54.620 --> 59:55.320
a tank

59:55.900 --> 59:57.480
and two questions.

59:57.800 --> 59:59.940
Five minutes in total. Am I allowed?

01:00:00.840 --> 01:00:01.800
Yes? No?

01:00:01.800 --> 01:00:04.000
No, if you can cut it down

01:00:04.000 --> 01:00:05.840
to 30 seconds, you're allowed.

01:00:06.160 --> 01:00:08.040
Ok, so I just go with my tank

01:00:08.040 --> 01:00:10.420
to the European Union

01:00:10.420 --> 01:00:11.880
about what

01:00:11.880 --> 01:00:13.560
Professor Poddy was saying. I say

01:00:13.560 --> 01:00:15.860
Professor because it's not

01:00:15.860 --> 01:00:17.980
so diplomatic today because he was

01:00:17.980 --> 01:00:19.920
very, very using

01:00:19.920 --> 01:00:21.960
a lot of feelings and we say today

01:00:21.960 --> 01:00:23.360
that he doesn't have

01:00:23.360 --> 01:00:25.800
good diplomatic, doesn't have feelings.

01:00:26.500 --> 01:00:27.300
But he was...

01:00:27.300 --> 01:00:29.440
But also Professor Sergei Sauer.

01:00:29.440 --> 01:00:30.740
Yes, of course.

01:00:32.180 --> 01:00:33.780
Ok, and I

01:00:33.780 --> 01:00:34.860
am representing

01:00:34.860 --> 01:00:37.220
eight international student organizations

01:00:37.220 --> 01:00:39.800
that are all European

01:00:39.800 --> 01:00:41.380
based and I would like to thank

01:00:41.380 --> 01:00:43.760
the European Union for the huge

01:00:43.760 --> 01:00:45.520
efforts that they have been doing

01:00:45.520 --> 01:00:46.740
and they are still doing

01:00:47.130 --> 01:00:49.240
to put our cultures together

01:00:49.240 --> 01:00:51.480
and to recognize all the cultures,

01:00:51.780 --> 01:00:53.920
the minorities that in Europe

01:00:53.920 --> 01:00:55.900
are living.

01:00:56.520 --> 01:00:57.640
And I would like

01:00:57.640 --> 01:00:59.360
to say just one thing about

01:00:59.360 --> 01:01:01.640
your comment about history, what we have

01:01:01.640 --> 01:01:03.080
to learn about history.

01:01:04.140 --> 01:01:04.760
The actual

01:01:05.500 --> 01:01:05.860
leading

01:01:07.640 --> 01:01:10.040
generation is teaching us

01:01:10.040 --> 01:01:12.080
to learn from their

01:01:12.080 --> 01:01:13.640
likes, to learn

01:01:13.640 --> 01:01:15.500
from their errors.

01:01:16.400 --> 01:01:17.800
And I'm glad

01:01:17.800 --> 01:01:19.620
in the name of eight

01:01:19.620 --> 01:01:21.360
international student organizations

01:01:21.360 --> 01:01:23.640
to thank the European Union also

01:01:23.640 --> 01:01:25.540
for their likes and for their errors

01:01:25.540 --> 01:01:27.740
because they are teaching us to be

01:01:27.740 --> 01:01:29.060
a better...

01:01:29.060 --> 01:01:31.320
to work for a better diplomacy

01:01:31.320 --> 01:01:33.420
and for a better democracy. Thank you.

01:01:33.700 --> 01:01:35.000
Thank you.

01:01:45.500 --> 01:01:47.340
Thank you. I'm Quinn Baer

01:01:47.340 --> 01:01:49.300
from Austria and I was here

01:01:49.300 --> 01:01:50.280
a student in 67.

01:01:51.480 --> 01:01:53.180
Since I'm a member...

01:01:53.180 --> 01:01:55.880
Close to your mouth please.

01:01:56.000 --> 01:01:57.160
Sir? Okay.

01:01:58.140 --> 01:01:59.680
Since I work for

01:01:59.680 --> 01:02:01.220
the government of a member state

01:02:01.220 --> 01:02:03.480
of the European Union, I have to

01:02:03.480 --> 01:02:05.480
correct Bob Evans' introduction

01:02:05.480 --> 01:02:07.400
of you because he introduced you

01:02:07.400 --> 01:02:09.340
as the president of the European Union.

01:02:09.800 --> 01:02:11.240
We all know of course you're the president

01:02:11.240 --> 01:02:12.420
of the European Commission.

01:02:13.240 --> 01:02:15.380
But anyway, this is not what I really want to say.

01:02:17.320 --> 01:02:19.000
My real question is

01:02:19.660 --> 01:02:21.380
you've been talking about

01:02:21.380 --> 01:02:23.500
Eastern enlargement, European enlargement

01:02:23.500 --> 01:02:24.760
towards the East.

01:02:26.500 --> 01:02:27.480
And my question is

01:02:27.480 --> 01:02:29.160
where do you see that Europe

01:02:29.160 --> 01:02:31.140
in the long run will end?

01:02:31.300 --> 01:02:33.360
Will it end at the application

01:02:33.360 --> 01:02:35.220
countries that we have

01:02:35.220 --> 01:02:36.980
now, these 12 countries,

01:02:37.440 --> 01:02:39.420
or will we go to Moldova or to

01:02:39.420 --> 01:02:40.940
Ukraine or even to Russia?

01:02:41.360 --> 01:02:43.860
Do you have any idea about that? Thank you.

01:02:44.760 --> 01:02:45.460
Oh, good.

01:02:47.500 --> 01:02:49.520
No, you are touching

01:02:49.520 --> 01:02:51.360
the real problem,

01:02:51.440 --> 01:02:53.120
one of the real problems.

01:02:53.640 --> 01:02:55.540
And I have

01:02:55.540 --> 01:02:57.520
a strong opinion, you know,

01:02:58.400 --> 01:02:59.340
for example, that Ukraine

01:02:59.340 --> 01:03:01.500
belongs to Europe for history

01:03:01.500 --> 01:03:03.500
and so on, Moldova belongs to Europe.

01:03:04.260 --> 01:03:05.820
But I also

01:03:05.820 --> 01:03:07.720
do know that you can't

01:03:07.720 --> 01:03:08.660
decide that.

01:03:09.300 --> 01:03:11.580
Now you need a big debate

01:03:11.580 --> 01:03:12.240
for that.

01:03:13.260 --> 01:03:15.400
I asked the European Parliament to start

01:03:15.400 --> 01:03:17.740
this debate, but nobody did

01:03:17.740 --> 01:03:19.460
because now we are so

01:03:19.460 --> 01:03:21.440
and it's correct, you know, we are so

01:03:21.440 --> 01:03:24.020
engaged in this process of enlargement

01:03:24.020 --> 01:03:25.580
that, you know,

01:03:25.820 --> 01:03:28.040
this debate has been in some way delayed.

01:03:30.820 --> 01:03:31.880
Well, it's a weakness,

01:03:32.080 --> 01:03:33.500
but I think it's wise.

01:03:37.120 --> 01:03:38.060
this is also

01:03:38.060 --> 01:03:39.640
one of the reasons why I am

01:03:39.640 --> 01:03:41.940
trying to do this enlargement

01:03:42.580 --> 01:03:43.900
with the due diligence

01:03:44.560 --> 01:03:45.040
needed

01:03:45.040 --> 01:03:47.360
and with all the efforts

01:03:47.360 --> 01:03:48.520
because

01:03:49.200 --> 01:03:51.220
then we have to start

01:03:51.220 --> 01:03:52.460
this debate.

01:03:52.980 --> 01:03:53.580
Certainly

01:03:55.800 --> 01:03:57.320
what surprises me

01:03:57.320 --> 01:03:59.160
is that

01:03:59.160 --> 01:04:01.180
the attraction of Europe is so strong,

01:04:01.180 --> 01:04:01.700
you know.

01:04:02.180 --> 01:04:05.040
I think that

01:04:06.440 --> 01:04:08.000
even in Switzerland

01:04:09.360 --> 01:04:11.060
there is no obligation, of course,

01:04:11.100 --> 01:04:12.700
but the problem is so open,

01:04:12.700 --> 01:04:14.980
so debated, so discussed

01:04:14.980 --> 01:04:17.080
and so it's

01:04:19.460 --> 01:04:21.100
important to do

01:04:21.100 --> 01:04:22.640
and in your country

01:04:22.640 --> 01:04:24.820
when I was in Austria

01:04:24.820 --> 01:04:25.560
recently

01:04:26.800 --> 01:04:28.760
I tried to meet

01:04:28.760 --> 01:04:30.600
not only politicians

01:04:30.600 --> 01:04:32.320
but also

01:04:32.320 --> 01:04:34.600
representatives of

01:04:34.600 --> 01:04:36.840
Austrian society, you know.

01:04:36.840 --> 01:04:37.920
And

01:04:40.920 --> 01:04:42.840
I met the

01:04:45.440 --> 01:04:47.160
two cardinals, the former

01:04:47.160 --> 01:04:49.000
and the existing one, you know.

01:04:49.100 --> 01:04:49.960
And they asked me

01:04:50.820 --> 01:04:52.540
but what do you think

01:04:52.540 --> 01:04:54.840
about Austria, the problems that

01:04:54.840 --> 01:04:55.980
we have in the enlargement?

01:04:57.120 --> 01:04:58.940
And my answer was very clear.

01:05:00.920 --> 01:05:01.520
Austria

01:05:03.240 --> 01:05:04.440
must be

01:05:04.440 --> 01:05:05.020
a protector

01:05:05.440 --> 01:05:07.940
The Austrian problem, you know,

01:05:08.200 --> 01:05:09.800
how you meet

01:05:09.800 --> 01:05:11.240
Austrian society together in this moment

01:05:11.240 --> 01:05:14.220
is giving a strong responsibility for the enlargement,

01:05:14.440 --> 01:05:15.340
a mission, you know.

01:05:15.580 --> 01:05:17.660
You are the most talented people

01:05:17.660 --> 01:05:20.660
who know better than anybody else

01:05:20.660 --> 01:05:22.600
from the Eastern countries.

01:05:23.260 --> 01:05:24.640
Vienna has always been

01:05:24.640 --> 01:05:26.780
a bridge between East and West

01:05:27.460 --> 01:05:29.020
and I think that

01:05:30.440 --> 01:05:32.520
a promise to give a positive mission

01:05:32.520 --> 01:05:34.520
to the country, to understand that

01:05:34.520 --> 01:05:36.820
this is, you know,

01:05:36.960 --> 01:05:38.800
increasing the potential of the country.

01:05:39.660 --> 01:05:41.080
I remember simply, you know,

01:05:41.180 --> 01:05:42.100
ten years ago,

01:05:42.440 --> 01:05:44.840
seven years ago, if you wanted to

01:05:44.840 --> 01:05:46.100
do any business

01:05:46.100 --> 01:05:48.580
with these countries, either you went to

01:05:48.580 --> 01:05:50.780
Kreditan Start or to some

01:05:50.780 --> 01:05:52.520
other Austrian bank.

01:05:52.640 --> 01:05:54.460
Only in Vienna you have expertise.

01:05:55.260 --> 01:05:56.600
And this is

01:05:56.600 --> 01:05:59.100
the real, you know,

01:05:59.580 --> 01:06:00.640
the real sense

01:06:00.640 --> 01:06:02.200
that you have a role

01:06:02.200 --> 01:06:04.460
in this phase of history.

01:06:05.240 --> 01:06:06.500
And then

01:06:06.500 --> 01:06:08.740
I said this because also in this conversation

01:06:08.740 --> 01:06:10.480
it was clear

01:06:11.640 --> 01:06:12.780
your question was

01:06:12.780 --> 01:06:14.300
repeated, you know,

01:06:14.360 --> 01:06:16.800
but where do you think to stop,

01:06:16.820 --> 01:06:18.660
you know, and came out

01:06:18.660 --> 01:06:21.080
from religious problems, cultural problems

01:06:21.080 --> 01:06:22.680
and you understand,

01:06:22.740 --> 01:06:24.320
you know, that this is important because

01:06:24.320 --> 01:06:26.420
also from the religious problem, Europe

01:06:26.420 --> 01:06:28.860
was born, let's say,

01:06:28.860 --> 01:06:30.240
dominated by the Catholic,

01:06:31.420 --> 01:06:33.000
then they were allowed into the Protestant,

01:06:33.280 --> 01:06:34.560
then to the Orthodox,

01:06:35.200 --> 01:06:36.720
then you have the problem to the

01:06:36.720 --> 01:06:37.660
religion with the Islamic,

01:06:38.860 --> 01:06:40.300
where is the border, you know.

01:06:40.420 --> 01:06:42.980
And I think that we must start

01:06:44.140 --> 01:06:45.180
this debate,

01:06:46.540 --> 01:06:47.080
not now,

01:06:47.080 --> 01:06:49.460
I don't understand that it's difficult to start it now,

01:06:49.960 --> 01:06:51.040
but this

01:06:51.040 --> 01:06:52.860
is one of the most important

01:06:54.700 --> 01:06:55.220
debates

01:06:55.220 --> 01:06:57.240
that we have to do in the European society,

01:06:57.240 --> 01:06:59.300
you know, and then we decide where to stop.

01:06:59.760 --> 01:07:01.740
Because if we don't do this,

01:07:02.180 --> 01:07:03.560
of course, I was joking

01:07:03.560 --> 01:07:05.060
but when somebody

01:07:05.060 --> 01:07:07.380
answered maybe your question, I answered

01:07:08.040 --> 01:07:09.680
well, if you take

01:07:09.680 --> 01:07:11.680
today's rules, South Korea

01:07:11.680 --> 01:07:13.460
is a typical country belonging to

01:07:13.460 --> 01:07:15.320
the European Union, because

01:07:15.320 --> 01:07:17.460
you know, inflation, so on and so on

01:07:17.460 --> 01:07:19.260
and so on and so on, you know, so

01:07:19.260 --> 01:07:21.400
this is why this debate is so important,

01:07:21.580 --> 01:07:23.320
because everybody thinks

01:07:23.920 --> 01:07:25.600
that there is a spirit,

01:07:25.600 --> 01:07:26.600
there is a history,

01:07:27.280 --> 01:07:29.240
you know, culture, but

01:07:29.820 --> 01:07:31.980
we have strictly defined it.

01:07:40.360 --> 01:07:41.560
My name is John Morton,

01:07:41.620 --> 01:07:43.020
I'm a current student at the Bologna Center.

01:07:43.420 --> 01:07:45.260
You mentioned that Europe is a

01:07:45.260 --> 01:07:47.240
organization of minorities, and

01:07:47.240 --> 01:07:49.580
whether or not it is today, it will certainly be that

01:07:49.580 --> 01:07:51.540
in the future, and you hit on the immigration

01:07:51.540 --> 01:07:53.140
issue briefly a moment ago.

01:07:53.140 --> 01:07:55.100
By conservative estimates,

01:07:55.440 --> 01:07:57.040
something on the order of 100 million

01:07:57.040 --> 01:07:59.300
new immigrants will need to come into the Union

01:07:59.300 --> 01:08:01.020
in the next 50 years.

01:08:01.880 --> 01:08:03.760
And I wonder from a policy perspective

01:08:03.760 --> 01:08:05.420
how the European Union and how

01:08:05.420 --> 01:08:07.600
you are going about proactively

01:08:07.600 --> 01:08:09.000
addressing that issue today,

01:08:09.480 --> 01:08:11.440
looking forward to the fact that there will be a mass

01:08:11.440 --> 01:08:13.440
influx of immigrants into the Union

01:08:13.440 --> 01:08:15.020
if current growth rates

01:08:15.020 --> 01:08:16.760
are to be maintained.

01:08:17.420 --> 01:08:19.360
The current growth rates,

01:08:21.260 --> 01:08:22.380
you know,

01:08:22.380 --> 01:08:24.380
in terms of

01:08:26.180 --> 01:08:27.800
economics, I am not worried.

01:08:28.860 --> 01:08:29.320
If you

01:08:29.940 --> 01:08:31.620
depend on this

01:08:31.620 --> 01:08:33.720
potential integration, of course,

01:08:33.900 --> 01:08:35.160
when I mentioned before,

01:08:35.480 --> 01:08:38.320
if you don't make big mistake,

01:08:38.500 --> 01:08:40.020
let's say, if you don't

01:08:40.020 --> 01:08:42.460
increase in one shot the Polish

01:08:42.460 --> 01:08:44.360
weight and salaries to the level

01:08:44.360 --> 01:08:45.820
of Germany, this type of mistake,

01:08:45.820 --> 01:08:48.640
that is possible, there is this

01:08:48.640 --> 01:08:50.280
need for distribution of work,

01:08:50.280 --> 01:08:52.660
for integration that

01:08:52.660 --> 01:08:54.220
potentially makes Europe

01:08:55.280 --> 01:08:56.680
a growth area

01:08:56.680 --> 01:08:58.540
with a large market.

01:08:59.580 --> 01:09:01.500
My worry is more on

01:09:01.500 --> 01:09:02.280
the political

01:09:03.360 --> 01:09:04.500
institutions, you know,

01:09:04.640 --> 01:09:06.420
and this is why I insisted so much

01:09:06.420 --> 01:09:08.600
in IDC, in the Intergovernmental

01:09:08.600 --> 01:09:10.400
Conference, in having

01:09:10.400 --> 01:09:12.320
new rules for solutions. Also,

01:09:12.900 --> 01:09:14.560
I didn't go into the details,

01:09:14.620 --> 01:09:17.140
but also the number of commissioners,

01:09:17.300 --> 01:09:18.660
how big can be the commission,

01:09:18.660 --> 01:09:20.560
you know, because it's, of course,

01:09:20.700 --> 01:09:22.240
now there are two commissioners per big

01:09:22.240 --> 01:09:24.060
member states and one for the small

01:09:24.060 --> 01:09:26.320
member states, so we should arrive

01:09:26.320 --> 01:09:28.480
if you don't change the rules with

01:09:28.480 --> 01:09:30.920
28 members, we should arrive to 37,

01:09:31.720 --> 01:09:32.800
38, you know,

01:09:33.180 --> 01:09:34.800
members of the commission, then how

01:09:34.800 --> 01:09:37.040
can you work? You can't work, you know.

01:09:37.060 --> 01:09:38.600
So, I'm more

01:09:38.600 --> 01:09:40.540
worried on how and then

01:09:40.540 --> 01:09:42.420
how we integrate

01:09:42.420 --> 01:09:44.540
the European Bank with

01:09:44.540 --> 01:09:46.260
economic institutions, so on and so on.

01:09:46.260 --> 01:09:48.200
We have all these institutional

01:09:48.200 --> 01:09:49.200
problems to tackle,

01:09:50.500 --> 01:09:52.100
but in terms of

01:09:52.100 --> 01:09:53.840
growth, I'm,

01:09:53.900 --> 01:09:56.420
I see, I don't see

01:09:56.420 --> 01:09:58.400
that there will be terrible

01:09:58.400 --> 01:10:00.300
problems, and this is also why

01:10:00.780 --> 01:10:01.840
we have this application

01:10:02.560 --> 01:10:04.420
of so many countries, you know.

01:10:05.240 --> 01:10:06.380
And then, you know,

01:10:06.480 --> 01:10:08.300
with the market of 500 million people

01:10:09.520 --> 01:10:10.080
integrated

01:10:11.940 --> 01:10:14.360
with the new institutions, I say, in Lisbon

01:10:14.360 --> 01:10:16.700
we decided really

01:10:16.700 --> 01:10:18.620
to get into the new technologies

01:10:18.620 --> 01:10:20.080
with a common policy.

01:10:21.320 --> 01:10:22.760
You will have an increase,

01:10:22.940 --> 01:10:24.400
an enormous increase in productivity.

01:10:25.460 --> 01:10:26.780
And I repeat, it's

01:10:26.780 --> 01:10:28.780
very interesting how

01:10:28.780 --> 01:10:30.780
all these countries make effort

01:10:30.780 --> 01:10:32.380
to adapt themselves to the new

01:10:32.380 --> 01:10:32.800
reality.

01:10:34.440 --> 01:10:36.600
There are a lot of problems inside that, you know,

01:10:37.800 --> 01:10:39.000
and it's

01:10:39.000 --> 01:10:39.960
not easy also

01:10:39.960 --> 01:10:41.940
to convince the Baltic countries

01:10:41.940 --> 01:10:44.380
that they must

01:10:44.380 --> 01:10:46.400
treat the Russian minority

01:10:46.400 --> 01:10:48.980
as well as they treat

01:10:48.980 --> 01:10:50.360
the population, you know,

01:10:51.000 --> 01:10:51.680
and, you know,

01:10:52.560 --> 01:10:54.140
but they do it, because otherwise

01:10:54.140 --> 01:10:56.820
they don't get into the Union, you know.

01:10:57.240 --> 01:10:58.040
But this is

01:10:58.040 --> 01:11:00.380
the real problem that we have to tackle

01:11:00.380 --> 01:11:02.000
now, you know, because they say, look,

01:11:02.100 --> 01:11:04.060
but we had so many problems for so

01:11:04.060 --> 01:11:05.960
many years, and now, now

01:11:05.960 --> 01:11:08.280
they are citizens as you are.

01:11:14.820 --> 01:11:16.760
My name is Yanis Karash

01:11:16.760 --> 01:11:18.140
and I'm a current student here.

01:11:18.740 --> 01:11:20.400
I'd like to ask if you'd like to be an elected

01:11:20.400 --> 01:11:21.720
president of the European Union.

01:11:21.720 --> 01:11:24.520
I would like to ask if you would like

01:11:24.520 --> 01:11:27.120
to be an elected president of the European Union

01:11:27.640 --> 01:11:29.340
and whether this could help solve

01:11:29.340 --> 01:11:30.580
the democratic deficit.

01:11:32.140 --> 01:11:32.620
Well,

01:11:34.120 --> 01:11:35.140
you've put the question

01:11:35.140 --> 01:11:36.840
in the right day. Yesterday

01:11:37.460 --> 01:11:38.560
the German foreign

01:11:38.560 --> 01:11:40.120
prime minister, foreign

01:11:40.960 --> 01:11:41.920
the German

01:11:41.920 --> 01:11:43.820
minister of foreign affairs, he proposed

01:11:43.820 --> 01:11:45.940
to have an elected

01:11:45.940 --> 01:11:47.820
European Union president.

01:11:48.120 --> 01:11:49.920
And I think it was a very bold

01:11:51.200 --> 01:11:51.860
proposition

01:11:51.860 --> 01:11:53.860
actually, you know, because sometimes

01:11:53.860 --> 01:11:55.620
elected by the

01:11:55.620 --> 01:11:58.000
parliament, but in some

01:11:58.000 --> 01:12:00.300
way the direct

01:12:01.320 --> 01:12:01.980
consequence

01:12:01.980 --> 01:12:03.920
of the democratic process

01:12:03.920 --> 01:12:06.200
he proposed elected by people, you know.

01:12:06.400 --> 01:12:07.800
And I found it very, very

01:12:07.800 --> 01:12:09.200
interesting, very challenging.

01:12:10.460 --> 01:12:11.600
It's not a problem

01:12:11.600 --> 01:12:13.500
today, but

01:12:14.040 --> 01:12:15.360
in any case

01:12:16.440 --> 01:12:17.380
the problem

01:12:17.380 --> 01:12:19.500
of filling up

01:12:19.500 --> 01:12:21.260
all the democratic deficit

01:12:21.260 --> 01:12:23.680
is important, is important.

01:12:24.400 --> 01:12:25.500
But, well, I forgot

01:12:25.500 --> 01:12:27.540
in my explanation to tell you that

01:12:27.540 --> 01:12:28.840
we have to avoid the confusion.

01:12:30.020 --> 01:12:31.480
When I talk

01:12:31.480 --> 01:12:33.440
about Europe, I never

01:12:33.440 --> 01:12:35.320
talk about, as I talk about

01:12:35.320 --> 01:12:37.360
the United States in the sense that

01:12:37.360 --> 01:12:39.760
I don't think there is such a big

01:12:39.760 --> 01:12:40.600
separate power.

01:12:42.540 --> 01:12:43.540
I asked for a paper

01:12:43.540 --> 01:12:45.120
on European governance

01:12:45.120 --> 01:12:47.540
in order to define what

01:12:47.540 --> 01:12:49.360
must be done in Brussels, what

01:12:49.360 --> 01:12:51.120
must be done at the national level,

01:12:51.340 --> 01:12:53.340
what must be done at the local level

01:12:53.340 --> 01:12:55.600
because I don't think to Europe

01:12:55.600 --> 01:12:57.200
as a centralized body.

01:12:58.400 --> 01:12:59.820
I think that Europe is necessary

01:12:59.820 --> 01:13:02.260
only in the fields in which

01:13:02.260 --> 01:13:03.020
globalization,

01:13:03.540 --> 01:13:05.360
common decision, you know,

01:13:05.360 --> 01:13:07.960
sense of unity must begin.

01:13:08.540 --> 01:13:09.700
But we have also to

01:13:09.700 --> 01:13:11.580
bring now a lot of

01:13:11.580 --> 01:13:13.360
decisions into the periphery.

01:13:15.360 --> 01:13:17.720
provided that, I think

01:13:19.660 --> 01:13:20.300
that

01:13:20.300 --> 01:13:21.400
I think that

01:13:22.360 --> 01:13:23.360
to fill up

01:13:23.360 --> 01:13:24.520
the democratic deficit

01:13:25.440 --> 01:13:27.500
we shall in some way go

01:13:27.500 --> 01:13:29.640
in that direction, but

01:13:29.640 --> 01:13:31.360
we need almost 50

01:13:31.920 --> 01:13:32.960
years for Europe

01:13:32.960 --> 01:13:34.780
to get that

01:13:34.780 --> 01:13:36.260
we shall need a long time.

01:13:36.780 --> 01:13:37.840
This is the direction.

01:13:48.540 --> 01:13:50.660
Signor Romano Prodi, my name is

01:13:50.660 --> 01:13:53.100
Alietto Guadagna, I'm a professor of international

01:13:53.100 --> 01:13:54.980
trade at Monocyrus

01:13:54.980 --> 01:13:56.640
at the center

01:13:56.640 --> 01:13:58.860
which was inaugurated by the University of Bologna

01:13:58.860 --> 01:14:00.800
two years ago. You have mentioned

01:14:00.800 --> 01:14:02.440
your meeting with President Clinton

01:14:03.200 --> 01:14:04.780
after the failure of the

01:14:04.780 --> 01:14:06.900
civil meeting. I would like

01:14:06.900 --> 01:14:08.820
to hear from you some impression about

01:14:08.820 --> 01:14:10.780
the future negotiation in the framework

01:14:10.780 --> 01:14:12.880
of the World Trade Organization.

01:14:19.740 --> 01:14:20.860
We do

01:14:20.860 --> 01:14:22.760
before I tell you what we are

01:14:22.760 --> 01:14:24.620
doing and then my focus,

01:14:24.780 --> 01:14:26.920
we are doing any effort

01:14:26.920 --> 01:14:29.020
to start again the negotiation

01:14:29.020 --> 01:14:31.340
because I think that you have to start

01:14:31.340 --> 01:14:32.040
them again.

01:14:32.860 --> 01:14:34.880
Our delegation is in China

01:14:35.740 --> 01:14:37.120
next week, I think

01:14:37.120 --> 01:14:39.240
no, today or next week.

01:14:41.380 --> 01:14:43.440
We want to be protagonist in this

01:14:43.440 --> 01:14:44.620
new talks.

01:14:46.840 --> 01:14:47.840
I don't know if they see

01:14:49.400 --> 01:14:50.020
or

01:14:50.020 --> 01:14:51.800
will be a difficulty

01:14:51.800 --> 01:14:53.020
in the sense that

01:14:55.060 --> 01:14:55.680
now

01:14:55.680 --> 01:14:57.380
the US

01:14:57.380 --> 01:14:59.960
administration is going to the end

01:14:59.960 --> 01:15:01.320
and it's difficult

01:15:01.320 --> 01:15:02.940
to resume

01:15:04.560 --> 01:15:05.120
the

01:15:05.120 --> 01:15:06.720
negotiations now

01:15:06.720 --> 01:15:09.860
but we are just working in this direction

01:15:09.860 --> 01:15:11.180
and especially

01:15:11.180 --> 01:15:13.380
we want to remove the problem of

01:15:13.380 --> 01:15:14.800
the big problem that is China

01:15:14.800 --> 01:15:17.380
first of all, you know, if you give a message

01:15:18.520 --> 01:15:19.640
referring to China

01:15:19.640 --> 01:15:21.340
is one billion, one hundred million

01:15:21.340 --> 01:15:23.240
people, I think that

01:15:23.240 --> 01:15:24.980
it would be a big change.

01:15:24.980 --> 01:15:27.440
But we have also to take

01:15:27.440 --> 01:15:28.340
responsibility

01:15:29.360 --> 01:15:31.300
for the least developed countries

01:15:31.300 --> 01:15:32.940
you know, it's not

01:15:32.940 --> 01:15:35.100
just demography, it's the problem of

01:15:36.240 --> 01:15:37.300
you know,

01:15:37.460 --> 01:15:39.020
if you want to be trusted

01:15:39.020 --> 01:15:41.380
you have to take responsibility.

01:15:51.720 --> 01:15:53.040
Thank you very much.

01:15:53.040 --> 01:15:54.860
There is a bias for the front

01:15:54.860 --> 01:15:56.460
speakers here.

01:15:56.740 --> 01:15:59.100
We have some up on the top over there.

01:16:00.800 --> 01:16:01.220
My name is

01:16:01.220 --> 01:16:02.940
Paul Hartig, I'm speaking

01:16:02.940 --> 01:16:05.500
on behalf of the Central European Initiative

01:16:05.500 --> 01:16:07.260
which I

01:16:07.260 --> 01:16:09.460
represent in its headquarters

01:16:09.460 --> 01:16:10.460
in Trieste.

01:16:11.500 --> 01:16:13.100
We have 16 member countries

01:16:13.100 --> 01:16:15.120
that's to say all the countries

01:16:15.120 --> 01:16:16.500
of Central and Eastern Europe

01:16:17.040 --> 01:16:18.860
from Austria to Ukraine

01:16:18.860 --> 01:16:21.080
and from Italy to Poland

01:16:21.080 --> 01:16:22.140
and so on.

01:16:23.000 --> 01:16:24.420
We see now

01:16:24.420 --> 01:16:26.260
particularly since you have mentioned

01:16:26.260 --> 01:16:28.660
the speech of the foreign minister

01:16:28.660 --> 01:16:30.540
of Germany yesterday

01:16:30.900 --> 01:16:32.880
that there is a lot of discussion

01:16:32.880 --> 01:16:35.060
going on within the

01:16:35.060 --> 01:16:37.100
European Union and its bodies

01:16:37.100 --> 01:16:39.040
on the future

01:16:39.040 --> 01:16:40.840
of this

01:16:40.840 --> 01:16:42.420
central

01:16:43.660 --> 01:16:45.220
political and

01:16:45.220 --> 01:16:46.800
economic force

01:16:46.800 --> 01:16:48.260
on the continent.

01:16:48.260 --> 01:16:50.540
It's a very open discussion

01:16:51.140 --> 01:16:52.020
and

01:16:52.940 --> 01:16:54.260
we have

01:16:54.260 --> 01:16:55.880
of course when you travel

01:16:55.880 --> 01:16:58.400
through all these capitals

01:16:58.400 --> 01:17:00.300
of Central and Eastern Europe

01:17:00.300 --> 01:17:02.760
until Ukraine, you have a feeling

01:17:02.760 --> 01:17:04.360
that you are of course

01:17:05.560 --> 01:17:06.440
getting

01:17:06.440 --> 01:17:08.520
further and further from

01:17:08.520 --> 01:17:09.580
the center.

01:17:10.420 --> 01:17:12.680
That's to say into a periphery

01:17:12.680 --> 01:17:14.420
where the contacts

01:17:14.420 --> 01:17:16.480
to this center become

01:17:16.480 --> 01:17:18.120
less and less

01:17:18.120 --> 01:17:19.460
strong.

01:17:20.600 --> 01:17:22.260
Of course now the Stability Pact

01:17:22.260 --> 01:17:24.320
for South Eastern Europe was

01:17:24.320 --> 01:17:26.140
a brilliant idea

01:17:26.140 --> 01:17:28.800
to strengthen

01:17:28.800 --> 01:17:30.120
the political,

01:17:30.580 --> 01:17:32.400
democratic, economic

01:17:32.400 --> 01:17:34.520
and so on

01:17:34.520 --> 01:17:35.420
relations

01:17:36.080 --> 01:17:38.760
within these countries and with the European Union.

01:17:40.580 --> 01:17:42.780
What I still feel

01:17:42.780 --> 01:17:44.280
is that

01:17:44.280 --> 01:17:46.660
the European Union does not

01:17:46.660 --> 01:17:48.380
sufficiently take

01:17:48.380 --> 01:17:50.740
into account the specific

01:17:50.740 --> 01:17:52.220
feelings

01:17:52.220 --> 01:17:54.240
of many of these countries.

01:17:54.920 --> 01:17:56.300
I've met recently someone

01:17:56.300 --> 01:17:58.140
who said we should

01:17:58.140 --> 01:18:01.000
establish a Balkan

01:18:01.000 --> 01:18:02.520
institute for a new

01:18:02.520 --> 01:18:03.020
Europe.

01:18:04.480 --> 01:18:06.340
And I later asked him whether he had made

01:18:06.340 --> 01:18:08.320
a mistake. Couldn't it be

01:18:08.320 --> 01:18:10.760
a European institute for a new Balkan?

01:18:11.120 --> 01:18:12.800
Excuse me, but is this

01:18:12.800 --> 01:18:14.480
the question? Yes.

01:18:14.560 --> 01:18:17.160
This is the question. Because it reflects

01:18:17.160 --> 01:18:19.120
an idea which I always

01:18:19.120 --> 01:18:20.400
feel to

01:18:20.400 --> 01:18:23.020
perceive that

01:18:23.020 --> 01:18:24.980
for instance the countries in

01:18:24.980 --> 01:18:26.880
these periphery areas

01:18:27.680 --> 01:18:28.460
do

01:18:28.460 --> 01:18:30.380
not understand,

01:18:30.600 --> 01:18:33.180
do not understand where the European

01:18:33.180 --> 01:18:34.820
Union is actually going.

01:18:35.680 --> 01:18:37.080
And at the same time

01:18:37.080 --> 01:18:38.840
one has to say that also

01:18:38.840 --> 01:18:41.100
the people, the populations

01:18:41.100 --> 01:18:43.220
in these countries have absolutely

01:18:43.220 --> 01:18:44.920
no idea

01:18:44.920 --> 01:18:47.020
of what the goals

01:18:47.020 --> 01:18:48.820
and objectives of the European Union are.

01:18:49.240 --> 01:18:51.340
But this is also a fact in

01:18:51.340 --> 01:18:53.260
the center, in the center of

01:18:53.260 --> 01:18:55.420
the European Union itself. Thank you.

01:18:55.640 --> 01:18:56.700
Well, I'm not surprised.

01:18:57.020 --> 01:18:58.900
There are even many things so strange

01:18:58.900 --> 01:19:01.140
they don't know where the European Union

01:19:01.140 --> 01:19:02.220
is going, you know.

